features.description: ACL based access control, determines maximum number of virtual workspaces for a customer
If enabled, allows to specify indicators based on workspace data.
Adds a number of metrics charts to the workspace, -1 = unlimited.
Allows to design and run surveys.
Adds more complex fields to survey and enables more options.
Allows to create and manage secure API tokens for the workspace in the administration area.
Allow admins to verify customer_roles in the administration of users in the workspace
Allows to opt in to derived data usage for the account in the administration area.
Allows to configure visual design of the workspace in the administration area.
Allows advance exporting of the workspace in the administration area. Additionally allows to monitor existing exports of the workspace.
Allows to edit settings of a Fact Sheet type for the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to build custom integrations for the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to build integration ecosystem for the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to toggle the visibility of the metrics configuration in the administration area.
Allows to configure workspace notifications in the administration area.
Allows to toggle the visibility of the portal configurations in the administration area.
Allows to install and manage reports for the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to configure settings of the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to toggle the visibility of the subscription roles configuration in the administration area.
Allows to visualize integrations logs of the workspace in the administration area.
Allow operations on technical users in the administration area.
Allows to use developer tools in the administration area.
Allows to exhange data with other systems for the workspace in the administration area.
Allows to configure workflows from the workflow service in the administration area.
Adds a search mechanism based on a machine learning allowing to do a semantic search for 'similar' Applications for the Self Service Portal.
Enables grouping of bookmarks into collections.
Defines a maximum amount of users a bookmark can be shared with.
Enables new BTM module.
Allows "Create new Fact Sheet" impacts to be defined.
Enables a completion date field on impact groups that is used as the timestamp in impacts executions and for the projection of the impacts in that impact group
Enables to send notification as E-Mail, disabling shuts down email for the workspace.
Enables admins to change the configuration of the meta model of a workspace, e.g. adding, removing fields, change translations, change order of objects or change basic configuration of FS types.

Preview-features to enable admins to change the configuration of the meta model of a workspace, e.g. adding, removing fields, change translations, change order of objects or change basic configuration of FS types.
Enables LeanIX Excel connector, convert Excel files to LeanIX Data Interchange Format (LDIF)
Allows to toggle the visibility of the menu entry for data privacy
Allows to upload logos and change colors of the workspace.
Shows powered by LeanIX in the Dashboard sidebar, if a custom logo has been uploaded for the menu.
Allows to add custom JavaScript snippets which are executed when application is loaded.
Shows the model editor in the administration area to support customizing.
Enables Data Flow in Diagrams
Enables draw.io XML export for Visualizer diagrams
Enables filter functionality in Diagrams
Enables Lucidchart integration
Enables the use of ArchiMate3 shapes in diagrams
Enables the use of AWS shapes in diagrams
Enables the use of Azure shapes in diagrams
Enables the use of GCP shapes in diagrams
Enables the use of Kubernetes shapes in diagrams
Enables the use of the export service based on headless Chrome
Allows to clone Fact Sheets.
Allows a user to create Fact Sheets with proposal names.
Defines the maximum level of Fact Sheet hierarchies.
Allows to remove the user from events that are older then the specified time in workspace settings.
Defines the maximum number of Fact Sheets in this workspace.
Limits the amount of applications a workspace can hold.
Enables management of lifecycles (activeFrom, activeTo) at Fact Sheet relations.
Only shows activeFrom/activeTo at Fact Sheet relations of the type applicationUserGroupRelation and applicationBusinessCapabilityRelation.
Allows to subscribe users to Fact Sheets.
Ignores to count Interfaces into the Fact Sheet quota.
Allows to upload images as a document at the Fact Sheet.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables Apptio Integration V2 (leanix-apptio-connector)
Enables Confluence Integration
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables the Integration API
Enables Intercom integration, allows customers to configure own Intercom App ID in workspace.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables Jira Integration v2.0.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Controls the availability of ltls-integration on leanix workspaces. LTLS integration works as an alternative to Technopedia integration.
Enables the LTLS Bulk Actions, linking multiple FactSheets to LTLS at once.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables Pivio Integration.
Make this integration visible/hidden in main panel of Integrations.
Enables ServiceNow Integration.
Enables advanced tab on ServiceNow Integration.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables advanced tab on Signavio Integration.
Enable multiple Signavio process mappings.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables Signavio Integration v2.0.
Enables Technopedia Integration v1.0.
Disables Technopedia credential check during configuration.
Make this integration visible in main panel of Integrations.
Enables the automatic recommendation of BusinessCapabilities based on descriptions of an Application.
Allows to configure the approval workflow with mandatory fields in the fact sheet type settings
Enables ODATA functionality via the import-export service.
Enables XLSX functionality via the import-export service.
Enables the quality check indicator at Fact Sheet and reminder notifications.
Enable inventory quick search grouping by Fact Sheet type
Enable the new inventory quick search
Saved bookmarks in inventory per user user workspace.
New way of searching, with changed behavior of facets.
Allows to edit Fact Sheet table view.
Enables the editing of relations and relation attributes in Inventory table view.
Enables language German.
Enables language English.
Enables language Spanish.
Enables language French.
Enables language Portuguese.
Enables to select language in the user profile and in the workspace settings.
Defines the maximum number of contacts per workspace, -1 = unlimited.
Defines the maximum number of users (incl. admins) per workspace, -1 = unlimited.
Defines the maximum number of viewers per workspace, -1 = unlimited.
If true, this workspace runs in an optimized mode for cloud native suite data processing.
With this quota you can limit how much cloud spent is managed in the workspace, -1 = unlimited
Enables the home screen and the collaboration features, e.g. comments at Fact Sheets.
Enables the APM dashboard.
Enables the calculation of indicators on the APM dashboard.
Enables the APM dashboard for Application Rationalization.
Enables a dashboard panel to include an iframe with external content to the dashboards.
Allows to include metrics panels in the dashboard
Enables the calculation of smart indicators within a workspace and to compare them across workspaces.
Enables the TRM dashboard for Management of technical debt.
Enables the calculation of indicators on the TRM dashboard.
Enables the to-do items that are created by a recommendation engine, e.g. inactive users.
Enables the to-do items that are workflow based, e.g. reminder at Fact Sheet, Open Comment or Survey.
Enables the display of legacy events which have been migrated from pre 4.0 version.
Sets the workspace in pathfinder active and enables notifications active from Pathfinder.
Enables configuration of Self-Service Portal.
Enables advanced configuration of Self-Service Portal (JSON based).
If enabled, the architecture roadmap is available in report creation.
Enables the use of edit pane in reporting.
Enables the use of report creation for admins.
Defines the maximum number of saved reports per user, -1 = unlimited.
Enables improved report navigation.
Enables the Technology Risk view in reports for Application Fact Sheets.
Allow users to toggle aggregation of interfaces
Allow users to configure visualizer shape for Fact Sheets
Enables integration with the LeanIX Store
Support levels for phone support: 0 - Comfort Support, 1 - Premium Support, 2 - Platinum Support
Allows navigation to a Skilljar-based training for regular LeanIX users.
Enables help tours in a workspace.
Enables intercom as default support chat, instead of support tab via email.
Enables to set tag groups as mandatory.
Allows to create and manage todos.
Enables user behaviour tracking powered by Pendo.
Allow users to create api token
Allow users to upload a profile picture
Enables users to invite other users to their workspace via email.
Allow operations on technical users
Triggers nightly execution of integration API processors for the KPIs that are shown on Application Rationalization dashboard
Triggers nightly execution of integration API processors for the KPIs that are shown on Technology Risk Management dashboard
Allow operations on workflows from the workflow service
Allow viewing of workspace-specific workflows from the workflow service
